scopeContent.description:
(1)"Photograph of Miss Mabel Moore, cabinet size No 43002-1, full length, kneeling profile with arms stretched out over draped table".

(2)"Photograph of Mrs F R Benson, whole plate size No 43003-3, full length, standing ¾ face holding curtains at each side".

(3)"Photograph of Mrs F R Benson, whole plate size No 43003-4, full length, standing ¾ face in drapery both arms raised holding wreath above head".

(4)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-2, full length group of two, Mr Benson kneeling with arms stretched over draped table, holding Miss Mabel Moore by her left hand, she standing holding staff in her right hand".

(5)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-5, group of three, Mrs Benson standing holding back curtain, showing a figure of a man & woman lying on ground".

(6)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-6, group of two, Mrs Benson kneeling on ground clutching Mr Benson by his clothes, he standing full length looking down at her".

(7)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-7, group of two, Mr Benson standing holding Mrs Benson by the throat, she standing with hands on breast".

(8)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-8, Mrs Benson standing on raised steps at back, men standing each side with arms outstretched towards her".

(9)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-10, group, woman kneeling on ground holding cloak, Mrs Benson standing as if pleading to man in armour, Miss Gertrude Scott standing at right of picture, other figures standing round mostly with arms up".

(10)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-11, group, Mrs Benson sitting on steps at back, a man holding shield & sword also standing on steps, groups of men each side holding staves & arms raised".

(11)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-12, group, Mrs Benson standing on steps at back holding curtain & looking over shoulder, a man in armour & helmet standing on her left & woman kneeling holding goblet on her right, two women kneeling on ground holding cloak, Miss Scott sitting at right of picture, some men grouped at left of picture".

(12)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-13, Mrs Benson standing on steps at back holding curtains & looking over shoulder, a man in armour & helmet standing on her left & a woman kneeling holding goblet on her right, two women kneeling on ground holding cloak, Miss Scott sitting at right of picture, Some men grouped at left".

(13)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-14, group, Mr Benson & Miss Mabel Moore kneeling each side of draped table, he touching it with his hands, she holding arm over it, figures grouped all round with arms raised".

(14)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-15, group, figures of a man & woman lying at back of stage, Mr Benson standing holding sword in left hand & pointing to the bodies with right hand, group of women at left of picture".

(15)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-16, group, figure wearing large white cloak holding the cloak out over arms looking down at figures of two women lying on ground, woman in centre with arm raised to pillar, other figures at back".

(16)"Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-17, group, Mr Keightley standing holding staff in left hand & touching Mr Benson with his right hand, a figure of a woman with snakes round her head kneeling by Mr Benson touching him, woman with snakes round her body & arms with one arm raised to pillar".
